  "esBriefingHtml": "<p style=\"margin-bottom:12px;\">Current GEX data shows we're in a stabilizing regime above gamma flip - expect dealers to buy dips and sell rallies, creating mean-reverting action. Both ES and NQ opened well above prior day value area (ES prev close 6944.60 vs current 6996.90), indicating initiative activity in progress. This breakout move needs confirmation through time spent at these elevated levels. Market Tide at neutral $0.0M suggests no institutional directional bias currently, making this a price-action driven session. No economic calendar risk today.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom:12px;\">ES ZONE MAP: <br>- 6999.40: Dark pool cluster ($543.3M across 8 prints) represents institutional cost basis just 2.50 points above current price. This is fresh accumulation that institutions will defend.<br>- 6945.80: Prior day high, now support after breakout. Failed reclaim signals weakness back to prior day low.<br>- 6876.60: Prior day low, major support zone 120 points below.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom:12px;\">ES TRADE PLAN: Long ES on any pullback to 6999.40 zone. This is fresh institutional accumulation (dark pool cluster) that creates natural buying support. Entry: 6999.40-6997.00. Stop: 6994.00 (below institutional defense zone). Target: 7020.00 (psychological resistance). R:R = 1.8:1. The size of this dark pool activity ($543M) indicates significant institutional commitment.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom:12px;\">WHAT TO IGNORE: Minor pullbacks above 7000.00, thin OI data, any break above 6999.40 without time confirmation.</p>",
